<br>
Out of my guild's melee, monks are the only class that consistantly use their epic.  The odd rogue has theirs offhanded, so do a few other classes, but in proportion - we even have a few of our newer warriors who offhand one of their epics.<br>
<br>
So to say the weapons aren't a stop gap for other classes isn't really true, while they may have a longer shelf life, they still get replaced except by monks (and maybe bards but their hard to box into a melee/caster category). <p><p align="center"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=15063" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.conclaveofshadows.co.uk/images/bnnrezb2.jpg" width="288" height="169" border="0"></a></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukhumak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Khumak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 62<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/25/02 12:13:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1316.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: upgrade to epic on test??</span><hr size=1> I would be opposed to upgrading the epic unless they fix the current bottleneck on it.  As it is now it is very hard to get but due to the stats on it most people already have better by the time they get it.  <br>
<br>
If it was improved so that it was even remotely on par with the cleric epic with respect to it's impact on raids then a triggerable version of Sev needs to be put in (probably one that ONLY drops the scale) so that the flow of warrior epics into the game is not determined by arbitrary spawn time but by the ability of the players to complete the quest.<br>
<br>
I'm quite sure my guild could kill Sev but I doubt we'll ever both see him up and be able to assemble enough people to go kill him before someone else does.<br>
<br>
If they are going to redo all of the epics then they need to change the limiting factor on how fast they are introduced into the game.  They should be limited by how hard the quest is to complete (difficulty of the mobs you need to kill), NOT by arbitrarily long spawn times.<br>
<br>
They should also be designed so that they retain roughly the same degree of usefulness as you progress through each stage of the game relative to the other epics.  If you're going to make some epics have a feature that makes it highly sought after years after it was released then they all should have some feature that makes them that sought after.  If not then all of them should be trivialized by some later upgrade.<br>
<br>
As it is now some class epics are used all the way through to the end game while others rot in the bank after a certain point.  That is poor designn IMHO. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=85547>Khumak</a><br>
60 Warrior<br>
Mith Marr<br>
(Imperial Guardians)</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uaveenlucenthawk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aveen Lucenthawk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/25/02 12:38:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1316.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: upgrade to epic on test??</span><hr size=1> Joshua,<br>
I am not trying to compare casters to melee mearly pointing out that the risk vs reward is off balance for the warrior epic in comparison to several other classes. If you want me to do melee epcis alone, lets examine the rogue epic. <br>
<br>
The rouge epic is not a bad weapon and many still use it but there are some better weapons out there for them, however, it is arguably one of the easiest epics to obtain the only difficult part being the general, and even then it is no longer that difficult. I have spoken to many people who obtained the rogue epic for their alt in one or two days. So for a decent weapon, it is apparently a very easy quest.<br>
However, the warrior epic is also a decent weapon but it often takes months to complete.  And do you ever see anyone tell the rogue not to use their epic or that it sucks? <br>
<br>
So you see, I was not intending to compare the power of the warrior epic to casters epics. I was comparing the ease of the quests vs the relative power (how good is that peice of equipment for the class it is designed for) of the epics.<br>
<br>
I origionally used the cleric epic in my example because it is arguably the most powerful epic in the game for its clickable rez and it was just made much, much easier to obtain. <br>
<br>
Aveen Lucenthawk<br>
Myrmidon of 58 Battles<br>
